opennlp.ccg.hylo.graph
Class LFEdgeLabel

java.lang.Object
  opennlp.ccg.hylo.graph.LFEdgeLabel

public class LFEdgeLabel
extends Object

A label for an LF edge. LF edge labels are drawn from Modes, so this class encapsulates one.

Since certain modes reoccur frequently, this class maintains a cache of modes mapped to edge labels, accessible via forMode(Mode).

Author:
Scott Martin

Method Detail

forMode

public static LFEdgeLabel forMode(Mode mode)
Gets a cached LF edge label for the specified mode, if one is available. If none has been created yet, a new LF edge label is created and cached for later use. Access to the cached LF edge labels is synchronized to avoid threading isues.

Parameters:
mode - The mode to create a label for.
Returns:
Either a cached LF edge label corresponding to the specified mode, if one is available, or a newly created one.
